<problem display_name="Which product?" linenum="198" tex_filename="./block2/matrixmult.tex" showanswer="finished" attempts="1" rerandomize="per_student">
  <text>
    <p>
Consider the matrices </p>
    <table id="a0000000109" class="equation" width="100%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="7" style="table-layout:auto">
      <tr>
        <td class="equation" style="width:80%;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;border-style:hidden">[mathjax]C = \left[\begin{array}{cc} 1 &amp;  -1 \\ 0 &amp;  2 \\ -1 &amp;  1 \end{array} \right].[/mathjax]</td>
        <td class="eqnnum" style="width:20%;vertical-align:middle;text-align:left;border-style:hidden"/>
      </tr>
    </table>
    <p>
 and </p>
    <table id="a0000000110" class="equation" width="100%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="7" style="table-layout:auto">
      <tr>
        <td class="equation" style="width:80%;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;border-style:hidden">[mathjax]D = \left[\begin{array}{ccc} 1 &amp;  2 &amp;  3 \\ 0 &amp;  1 &amp;  1 \\ -1 &amp;  4 &amp;  3 \end{array} \right][/mathjax]</td>
        <td class="eqnnum" style="width:20%;vertical-align:middle;text-align:left;border-style:hidden"/>
      </tr>
    </table>
    <p>
Of [mathjaxinline]CD[/mathjaxinline] and [mathjaxinline]DC[/mathjaxinline], which matrix product is defined? </p>
    <p>
      <optionresponse>
        <optioninput options="('CD','DC','Both are defined')" correct="DC"/>
      </optionresponse>
    </p>
    <p>
      <solution>
        <font color="blue">Answer: </font>
        <font color="blue">
          <p>
 Since [mathjaxinline]D[/mathjaxinline] has 3 rows, and [mathjaxinline]C[/mathjaxinline] has only 2 columns, [mathjaxinline]CD[/mathjaxinline] is undefined. But, [mathjaxinline]C[/mathjaxinline] has 3 rows, and [mathjaxinline]D[/mathjaxinline] has 3 columns, and thus the product [mathjaxinline]DC[/mathjaxinline] is defined. </p>
        </font>
      </solution>
    </p>
  </text>
</problem>
